Thank you for your submission! We really appreciate it. Like many open source projects, we ask that you sign our [Contributor License Agreement](https://cla-assistant.io/TokTok/c-toxcore?pullRequest=2162) before we can accept your contribution.
You have signed the CLA already but the status is still pending? Let us [recheck](https://cla-assistant.io/check/TokTok/c-toxcore?pullRequest=2162) it.

@snyk-bot, you are drunk. `bullseye-slim` is the same as `11-slim`, so this PR changes nothing :\

>[Stable releases are also tagged with their version (ie, `debian:9` is an alias for `debian:stretch`, `debian:8` is an alias for `debian:jessie`, etc).](https://hub.docker.com/_/debian)

>debian:bullseye-slim
>[DIGEST:sha256:fa4209bc498f3cf557c7d448f295d300aed44e7fd296fdd480a8ff5785cca305](http://web.archive.org/web/20220318224120/https://hub.docker.com/layers/debian/library/debian/bullseye-slim/images/sha256-fa4209bc498f3cf557c7d448f295d300aed44e7fd296fdd480a8ff5785cca305?context=explore)

>debian:11-slim
>[DIGEST:sha256:fa4209bc498f3cf557c7d448f295d300aed44e7fd296fdd480a8ff5785cca305](https://web.archive.org/web/20220318224213/https://hub.docker.com/layers/debian/library/debian/11-slim/images/sha256-fa4209bc498f3cf557c7d448f295d300aed44e7fd296fdd480a8ff5785cca305?context=explore)

>The following vulnerabilities are fixed with an upgrade:

Huh. It claims that CVE-2021-4209 is fixed in Debian 11 (Bullseye) [but it isn't](http://web.archive.org/web/20220318225210/https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2021-4209).

It also lists SNYK-DEBIAN11-UTILLINUX-2401081 (CVE-2022-0563) twice for some reason, which also [hasn't been fixed in Bullseye yet](http://web.archive.org/web/20220318225505/https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2022-0563).
